-- Princeton Among 15 Schools Awarded for Retired-Faculty Support
-- B y   J e a n n a   S m i a l e k
-- 2012-06-19T15:49:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-19/princeton-among-15-schools-awarded-for-retired-faculty-support.html
Princeton University , Wellesley
College and the University of Baltimore are among 15 schools
awarded grants for their support of faculty transitioning to
retirement.  The schools will receive $100,000 each from the Alfred P.
Sloan Foundation in conjunction with the American Council on
Education, according to a  statement  released yesterday. The
funds will be used by the institutions to further their
practices.  The winners work with professors to develop legacies before
they stop working, aid in the transition to retirement and help
retirees remain engaged in higher education.  The other recipients were Albright College, Carleton
College, Mount Holyoke College, Skidmore College,  Bentley
University , San Jose State University, Xavier University, George
Mason University, Georgia Institute of Technology,  University of
California  at Davis, University of Southern California and the
University of Washington.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jeanna Smialek in New York at 
 jsmialek@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
